policy on hateful content

00:20:17.190 --> 00:20:21.750
in 2020, the year Ohanian left
the company. Lessons learned,

00:20:21.750 --> 00:20:24.960
Ohanian is now taking another
stab at social media.

00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:26.280
He and the former CEO

00:20:26.280 --> 00:20:29.430
of Digg Kevin Rose, once arch rivals, are

00:20:29.430 --> 00:20:31.020
teaming up to revive Digg.

00:20:31.020 --> 00:20:33.810
I mean, I really disliked
you for a long time

00:20:33.810 --> 00:20:35.430
and rightfully so,

00:20:36.690 --> 00:20:38.640
Which has been rebranded as a community

00:20:38.640 --> 00:20:40.920
with humanity at its core.

00:20:40.920 --> 00:20:42.270
But humanity doesn't seem

00:20:42.270 --> 00:20:44.610
to attract eyeballs much these days.

00:20:44.610 --> 00:20:47.020
If the engine of virality is extremism

00:20:47.020 --> 00:20:49.420
and Digg is supposed to be the antidote,

00:20:49.420 --> 00:20:51.010
how do you drive engagement?

00:20:51.010 --> 00:20:55.570
I think what we found in authentic human

00:20:55.570 --> 00:20:58.960
online community is it's the last bastion

00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:01.870
of really high quality content.

00:21:01.870 --> 00:21:04.840
And so whether you want to
know an opinion about a movie,

00:21:04.840 --> 00:21:07.300
whether you want to know
about a camera to buy,

00:21:07.300 --> 00:21:10.360
there is always gonna be
real, real value there.

00:21:10.360 --> 00:21:15.360
But what I worry about is there
is this, this flywheel of,

00:21:15.400 --> 00:21:18.310
you know, if we know these
models are trained on content

00:21:18.310 --> 00:21:20.320
that are now largely botted

00:21:20.320 --> 00:21:22.090
or AI generated, you know

00:21:22.090 --> 00:21:24.520
that authenticity loop
breaks down real quick

00:21:24.520 --> 00:21:26.740
and that that trust
breaks down real quick.

00:21:26.740 --> 00:21:29.860
There clearly needs to be some
other version of, you know,

00:21:29.860 --> 00:21:31.060
if you just want to show up

00:21:31.060 --> 00:21:34.330
and you know, find a community
of people who love cameras,

00:21:34.330 --> 00:21:36.910
where do you go to get authentic,

00:21:36.910 --> 00:21:38.560
real human reviews of those

00:21:38.560 --> 00:21:40.150
things?

00:21:40.150 --> 00:21:42.280
In a world increasingly crowded by bots

00:21:42.280 --> 00:21:46.480
and algorithms, Ohanian is once
again betting on community,

00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:49.630
on the pitch, the track, in our cities

00:21:49.630 --> 00:21:53.140
and even in social media.
The question now becomes,

00:21:53.140 --> 00:21:56.620
can a master of marketing
sell us back on authenticity?

00:21:57.490 --> 00:21:59.860
What advice would you give founders today

00:21:59.860 --> 00:22:02.260
that's different than
what you got back then?

00:22:02.260 --> 00:22:05.620
The biggest advice which
Paul Graham put on everyone's

00:22:05.620 --> 00:22:07.090
shirt, and I think it still holds true,

00:22:07.090 --> 00:22:09.130
which is make something people want.

00:22:09.130 --> 00:22:10.720
In 20 years

00:22:10.720 --> 00:22:12.820
now I can say having
started multiple companies,

00:22:12.820 --> 00:22:14.560
seeded many, many more,

00:22:14.560 --> 00:22:16.360
that founding principle never goes away.

00:22:16.360 --> 00:22:19.510
I think the founders for
today need to know just

00:22:19.510 --> 00:22:20.950
how much responsibility they have.

00:22:20.950 --> 00:22:25.810
So I would say move
decisively. Move earnestly.

00:22:25.810 --> 00:22:27.250
Be aware of what you're building

00:22:27.250 --> 00:22:30.280
and know that like this
responsibility starts right now

00:22:30.280 --> 00:22:32.830
for building something that is
gonna have a very big impact

00:22:32.830 --> 00:22:33.663
on the world.

